% - threadmain() vs main(): no thread library preamble needed in OCaml
% - proccreate for filsysproc: OCaml threads do not block each other, so no separate proc needed
% - cexecpipe(): OCaml uses Unix2.pipe directly, no need for OCEXEC workaround
% - xfidinit() worker pool: OCaml creates threads on the fly (Thread.create in Read/Write dispatch)
% - channel creation section: channels are created where they are used, not in a separate section
