%******************************************************************************
\chapter{Cursors}
%******************************************************************************
\label{chap:cursor}

%claude:
[[rio]] uses different cursor shapes to give visual feedback about
window management operations: a cross when sweeping a new window,
a box when moving, a sight when selecting a window to delete.
Around window borders, the cursor changes to an arrow pointing
toward the nearest edge or corner, hinting at resize directions.

\section{Cursor graphics}

\subsection{Classic cursors}

%claude:
Each cursor is defined as a pair of 16x16 bitmaps ([[clr]] and
[[set]]) plus a hotspot offset. The [[clr]] bitmap defines the
shape (where the cursor is non-transparent), and [[set]] defines
which pixels within that shape are black vs.\ white.

<<signature [[Cursors.crosscursor]]>>=
val crosscursor : Cursor.t
@
<<signature [[Cursors.boxcursor]]>>=
