\section{Window creation}

%claude:
Creating a new window is a three-step process:
(1)~the user sweeps a rectangle on screen with the mouse,
(2)~[[rio]] allocates a [[Window.t]], a layer on the desktop,
and a new window thread,
(3)~[[rio]] forks a child process, sets up its namespace
(mount + bind) so it sees virtual devices, and execs the shell.

