kernel's draw device under the name [["window.<id>"]]. This is
essential: when the child process calls [[Draw.init]], the library
reads [[/dev/winname]] (served by [[rio]]) to discover this name,
then uses it to look up the layer. Without this call, the client
would have no way to find its window's image.

<<[[Wm.new_win()]] when parent in fork with [[pid]] child>>=
